#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:1
msgid "Local Development"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:3
msgid ""
"This guide covers setting up the full local development environment: the "
"Linked Data Explorer frontend and its backend. Both must run simultaneously "
"because the frontend calls the backend for all SPARQL and Operaton "
"operations."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:7
msgid "Prerequisites"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:9
msgid "Node.js 20.0.0 or higher"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:10
msgid "npm 10.0.0 or higher"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:11
msgid "Git"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:12
msgid ""
"Access to the TriplyDB and Operaton remote services (no local setup needed — "
"they are always available remotely)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:16
msgid "Setup"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:18
msgid ""
"# 1. Clone the repository\n"
"git clone https://github.com/sgort/linked-data-explorer.git\n"
"cd linked-data-explorer\n"
"\n"
"# 2. Install all workspace dependencies\n"
"npm install"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:29
msgid "Backend configuration"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:31
msgid ""
"cd packages/backend\n"
"cp .env.example .env"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:36
msgid "Edit `.env`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:38
msgid ""
"# Server\n"
"NODE_ENV=development\n"
"PORT=3001\n"
"HOST=localhost\n"
"\n"
"# CORS — must include both frontend dev ports\n"
"CORS_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3000,http://localhost:5173\n"
"\n"
"# TriplyDB — default SPARQL endpoint\n"
"TRIPLYDB_ENDPOINT=https://api.open-regels.triply.cc/datasets/stevengort/DMN-"
"discovery/services/DMN-discovery/sparql\n"
"TRIPLYDB_TIMEOUT=30000\n"
"\n"
"# Operaton\n"
"OPERATON_BASE_URL=https://operaton.open-regels.nl/engine-rest\n"
"OPERATON_TIMEOUT=10000\n"
"\n"
"# Logging\n"
"LOG_LEVEL=debug\n"
"LOG_FORMAT=json\n"
"\n"
"# Performance\n"
"CHAIN_EXECUTION_TIMEOUT=5000\n"
"MAX_CHAIN_DEPTH=10\n"
"ENABLE_CACHING=false"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:67
msgid "PostgreSQL setup (local)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:69
msgid ""
"For local development, reuse the `ronl-postgres` container already running "
"as part of the RONL Business API stack. Create the LDE database and user "
"once:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:70
msgid ""
"docker exec -it ronl-postgres psql -U postgres -c \\\n"
"  \"CREATE USER lde_user WITH PASSWORD 'lde_password';\"\n"
"\n"
"docker exec -it ronl-postgres psql -U postgres -c \\\n"
"  \"CREATE DATABASE lde_assets OWNER lde_user;\"\n"
"\n"
"docker exec -it ronl-postgres psql -U postgres -c \\\n"
"  \"GRANT ALL PRIVILEGES ON DATABASE lde_assets TO lde_user;\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:81
msgid "Then add to `packages/backend/.env`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:82
msgid ""
"DATABASE_URL=postgresql://lde_user:lde_password@localhost:5432/lde_assets"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:86
msgid ""
"The migration runs automatically on `npm run dev` startup. Look for `[DB] "
"Migrations applied` in the console."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:88
msgid "To verify the tables were created:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:89
msgid ""
"docker exec -it ronl-postgres psql -U lde_user -d lde_assets -c \"\\dt\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:93
msgid ""
"If `DATABASE_URL` is absent, the backend logs `[DB] Skipping migrations — "
"database not configured` and continues without asset storage — localStorage "
"fallback remains fully functional for development."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:95
msgid ""
"!!! note \"Shared container, isolated database\" The `ronl-postgres` "
"container hosts multiple databases. The LDE uses `lde_assets` with a "
"dedicated `lde_user` scoped to that database only. The RONL Business API "
"uses `audit_logs` with `audit_user`. The two databases are fully isolated."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:100
msgid "RoPA Records — local setup"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:102
msgid "Seed example records"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:104
msgid ""
"After the database is running and the backend has started (tables created by "
"migration), seed the four example RoPA records from `packages/backend`:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:105
msgid ""
"cd packages/backend\n"
"npx ts-node --project tsconfig.json src/db/seed-ropa.ts"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:110
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\local-development.md:110"
msgid "Expected output:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:111
msgid ""
"[seed-ropa] Seeding RoPA records…\n"
"[seed-ropa] AwbShellProcess (Flevoland) → <uuid>\n"
"[seed-ropa] TreeFellingPermitSubProcess → <uuid>\n"
"[seed-ropa] AwbZorgtoeslagProcess → <uuid>\n"
"[seed-ropa] ZorgtoeslagProvisionalSubProcess → <uuid>\n"
"[seed-ropa] Done."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:120
msgid ""
"The seed is idempotent — re-running it updates existing rows in place via "
"`ON CONFLICT (bpmn_process_id) DO UPDATE`. It is safe to run multiple times."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:122
msgid "Verify records in the database"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:123
msgid ""
"docker exec -it ronl-postgres psql -U lde_user -d lde_assets \\\n"
"  -c \"SELECT bpmn_process_id, process_level, status FROM ropa_records ORDER "
"BY process_level;\""
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:128
msgctxt "C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer\\developer\\local-development.md:128"
msgid "Expected output:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:129
msgid ""
"bpmn_process_id          | process_level | status\n"
"----------------------------------+---------------+--------\n"
" AwbShellProcess                  | shell         | active\n"
" AwbZorgtoeslagProcess            | shell         | active\n"
" TreeFellingPermitSubProcess      | subprocess    | active\n"
" ZorgtoeslagProvisionalSubProcess | subprocess    | active\n"
"(4 rows)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:139
msgid "Verify the public endpoint"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:140
msgid ""
"curl \"http://localhost:3001/v1/ropa/public?organisation=flevoland\" | jq "
"'.data | length'"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:144
msgid ""
"Should return `4`. If you get `0`, the `controller_name` values in the "
"seeded records do not contain \"flevoland\" — re-run the seed after "
"verifying the controller names in `src/db/seed-ropa.ts`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:146
msgid "Test the public site locally"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:148
msgid ""
"`packages/ropa-site/index.html` has the API URL hardcoded. For local "
"development change it to the local backend:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:149
msgid ""
"const API_URL =\n"
"  'http://localhost:3001/v1/ropa/public?organisation=flevoland';"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:154
msgid "Open the file directly in a browser (`file://`) or serve it:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:155
msgid ""
"cd packages/ropa-site\n"
"npx serve ."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:160
msgid ""
"!!! warning \"CORS when opening as file://\" When `index.html` is opened "
"directly from disk, the browser sends `Origin: null`. The global CORS "
"middleware rejects `null` origins. The path-aware CORS fix in `index.ts` "
"that serves `/v1/ropa/public` with `origin: '*'` bypasses this — but only if "
"that fix is in place. If you see a CORS error when opening from `file://`, "
"confirm `index.ts` has the path-aware cors middleware, not just the route-"
"level cors in `ropa.public.routes.ts`."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:163
msgid ""
"!!! note \"Revert before committing\" Remember to revert `const API_URL` to "
"the ACC or production URL before committing `packages/ropa-site/index.html`."
msgstr ""

