#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:205
msgid "Docker readiness check (v1.5.1+)"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:207
msgid ""
"Before starting the backend, the `npm run dev` script in `packages/backend` "
"runs `scripts/check-docker.sh`. The script verifies the `ronl-postgres` "
"container is up and healthy, fails fast with a clear remediation message if "
"not, and prevents nodemon from starting against a broken database."
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:209
msgid "Coloured output:"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:211
msgid "**Green** — container is running and healthy → dev server starts"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:212
msgid ""
"**Yellow** — container is running but not yet healthy (still initialising) → "
"wait briefly and retry"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:213
msgid ""
"**Red** — container is missing, stopped, or Docker daemon not running → "
"script prints the exact `docker start` or `docker run` command for the "
"missing container and exits non-zero"
msgstr ""

#: C:/Users/gorts01/Development/iou-architectuur/docs/en/linked-data-explorer%5Cdeveloper%5Clocal-development.md:215
msgid ""
"If you bypass the check (e.g. running `nodemon` directly), the backend will "
"still try to migrate against `DATABASE_URL` and you'll get a connection "
"error at startup. Just run `npm run dev` instead."
